@component server-relay
@intent A2A relay + routing sub-module of the Constellation live-board `server` family (v1.1 split per phase_2 2026-06-04). Owns the multi-agent routing core: (a) agent registration via HELLO+agentId (anonymous HELLO held at transport but never registered — §13.16.4 unauthorized-probe gate), (b) §13.8 reply-window pairing (`_a2aPending` Map; responder backfills `targetAgentId`/`contextId`/`parentId` from pending request within 120s window for adapters that can't echo the A2A envelope), (c) telemetry exclusion (codex-watch threadId/runId → board fan-out only, never bound into reply-window — see ws-core §13.16.6 element 1 filter family), (d) server-stamped source truth (`sourceStampFallback` — server is authoritative for `source` role on board-fanout/record paths; client-set `source` preserved when present, server stamps when client omits), (e) `targetAgentId` value-nested fallback for client envelope shape mismatch (silent_disable principle — acceptance broadened, mismatch surfaced via single warning), (f) graceful main handoff (axis 2 `@machine` — STABLE ↔ HANDOFF_PENDING with 10s timeout fallback), (g) orchestration message dispatch (`wsHandleOrch` — SetMain/HandoffReady + key admin delegated to `-keys`), (h) §13.19 deadlock observation layer (`wsBuildWaitEdges` / `wsDetectCycles` / `wsSurfaceEscalation` / `wsEffectiveElapsed` / `wsWaitState` + outbound hooks + probe sweep), (i) UI6 SelectionPrompt/Answer/Cancel routing (`_selPrompts` + `wsSelResolved` + `UI6_SERVER_TTL_MS` hard-TTL sweep).
@expansion temperature=0.2 model=agent/claude template=estreux/v0.1
@targets vanilla
@profile backend-service
@source constellation/reference/runtime/server.cjs(L414-625 §13.19 deadlock observation layer · L670 · L674-678 · L795-796) · constellation/reference/runtime/server.cjs(L159-160 · L382-385 · L681-690 · L733-734 · L736-758 · L778-787 UI6 SelectionPrompt) · constellation/reference/runtime/server.cjs(L267-300 wsCommit · wsSetMain · wsHandoffReady · wsHandleOrch dispatch)
@state
  A2A_WINDOW       : number = 120000    # §13.8 reply-window fallback (ms)
  UI6_SERVER_TTL_MS: number              # SelectionPrompt hard-TTL sweep window (see ref impl)
  wsAgents         : Map<agentId, conn>  # registered agents (HELLO+agentId); same id re-connect replaces prior
  WS_PRIMARY_ID    : string = env.WS_PRIMARY_AGENT || 'main-agent'   # current main (orchestrator)
  _a2aPending      : Map<agentId, {from, contextId, parentId, at}>   # §13.8 reply-window pairing
  _pendingMain     : string = null       # handoff target awaiting HandoffReady (10s timer)
  _selPrompts      : Map<promptId, {agentId, body, ttl}>             # UI6 SelectionPrompt server-side TTL store
  _DEADLOCK_*      : (consts)            # §13.19 detection thresholds + classification gates
@deps
  ws-core    : conn registry + event() builder
  -core      : constellation/server-core.eux (provides classified conn from upgrade; wsConns + connection_role machine)
  -keys      : constellation/server-keys.eux (orchestration delegates Register/Revoke* to -keys)
  -history   : constellation/server-history.eux (relay path calls record() on every relayed/broadcast message)
@ports
  cmd  register(HELLO, conn)                          : require msg.agentId else ANON_PROBE gate; close+replace prior conn for same agentId; wsAgents.set; wsPushAgentList
  cmd  relay(msg, fromConn)                            : §13.8 reply-window pairing + telemetry exclusion + source/target fallback; ALWAYS wsToBoards + wsRecord (via -history)
  cmd  setMain(toAgentId)                              : arm handoff axis 2 (HandoffRequested + 10s timer)
  cmd  handleOrch(msg, conn)                           : dispatch — SetMain/HandoffReady stay here; Register/Revoke* delegated to -keys
  out  AgentListBroadcast(agents[])                    # wsPushAgentList after register/close
  out  MainChanged(from, to)                           # after wsCommitMain (axis 2)
  out  ServerNoticeBroadcast(kind, payload)            # online/offline/restart-pending broadcasts
  out  DeadlockEscalationSurfaced(decisionId, edges)   # §13.19 wsSurfaceEscalation board surface
@wire
  source_stamp_truth:
    rule: server stamps `msg.source` from `conn.meta.role` on board-fanout/record paths when client omits; client-set source preserved
    rationale: dashboard's m.source==='agent'|'user'|'board' checks become server-truth, not client-honor (Report 2 Finding 1 — worker join unclassified entire session because dashboard relied on client field client never set)
  target_fallback:
    rule: if msg.targetAgentId unset but msg.value?.targetAgentId set → backfill from value + warn
    silent_disable_principle: acceptance broadened, mismatch surfaced (see Constellation.md §2 AgentHello shape literal)
@routing
  groups: A2A-intent (relay-able) · board-directed (UI control) · handshake (HELLO/SERVER_HELLO/AgentHello/OnboardAck) · notice (ServerNotice/Heartbeat/PersistentAdapterSmoke/Typing/AgentList)
  telemetry_exclude:
    require_tag: threadId/runId == 'codex-watch' OR STATE_SNAPSHOT.scope == 'codex-watch'
    excluded_from: [A2A reply-window pairing, main routing]      # board broadcast only
  a2a_priority_head_of_queue: per §13.16.8 outbound A2A + prerequisites run FIRST (enforced at agent side; server respects ordering)
  anonymous_gate: relay skip entirely if conn.meta.anonymous (HELLO without agentId class)
@behavior
  register(HELLO)  : missing agentId → anonymous gate (origin log only, no agent registry write); present → role=agent + agentId + clientId + agentName + key-role meta; close+replace prior conn for same agentId; wsAgents.set; wsPushAgentList
  relay            : anonymous skip; targetAgentId present & registered → send to that agent + _a2aPending.set(tgt, {from, context, parent, at}); else reply-window fallback (THIS sender has pending A2A within A2A_WINDOW AND msg not telemetry/ConnectionRestored → backfill from pending + relay to original requester only if alive & d!==conn; RUN_FINISHED closes pairing); else target-unspecified CUSTOM (not telemetry, name!='ConnectionRestored') → WS_PRIMARY_ID (if p!==conn); ALWAYS wsToBoards(msg) + wsRecord(msg via -history)
  sourceStampFallback : before wsToBoards/wsRecord, if msg.source unset → stamp from conn.meta.role
  targetFallback   : if msg.targetAgentId unset but msg.value?.targetAgentId set → fallback + warn single line
  dropTransient    : Heartbeat / PersistentAdapterSmoke / Typing → swallow (no relay, no record)
  serverNotice     : ServerNotice → wsToAll(agents+boards) + wsRecord (online/offline/restart broadcast)
  boardInbound     : non-agent conn — CloseChannel → -history wsCloseChannelHist + notify boards; RequestChannelHistory → -history wsLoadChannel → ChannelHistory; ArchiveChannel → -history wsArchiveChannel; UserPrompt atts → -core storeAtt. Route to targetAgentId else WS_PRIMARY_ID; mirror to other boards (sender excluded); wsRecord
  setMain          : if to≠current & registered → send current main HandoffRequested{to, reason}; _pendingMain=to; arm 10s timer → wsCommitMain
  handoffReady     : HandoffReady → clear timer → wsCommitMain immediately
  commitMain       : WS_PRIMARY_ID=to; wsPushAgentList; broadcast MainChanged (server uninterrupted — only role/authority moves)
  deadlock_observation_§13_19:
    detect: wsBuildWaitEdges (waitingOn/ackFor/targetAgentId parse from inbound A2A) → wsDetectCycles (naive DFS strict/quasi classification)
    surface: wsSurfaceEscalation → board EscalationSurfaced{decisionId=esc-msgId, edges}
    cadence: probe sweep + wsEffectiveElapsed time correction; ReviewSLAAck no-auto-emit (agent-side)
    state_machine: wsWaitState per §13.19.9 (WAITING → ESCALATED → RESOLVED transitions)
  ui6_selection_prompt:
    issue: agent emits SelectionPrompt{promptId, body, audience?, ttl?} → _selPrompts.set + relay to audience
    answer: user emits SelectionAnswer{promptId, choice} → wsSelResolved → relay to original agent
    cancel: agent emits SelectionCancel{promptId} → _selPrompts.delete + notify audience
    hard_ttl_sweep: UI6_SERVER_TTL_MS expiry → wsSelResolved with timeout outcome
@machine main_handoff
  # reducer: (mainState, event) → mainState — axis 2 of original two-axis @machine
  initial: STABLE
  states:
    STABLE:
      on:
        SetMain{to} → HANDOFF_PENDING    # entry: HandoffRequested → current main; arm 10s timer
    HANDOFF_PENDING:
      on:
        HandoffReady → STABLE              # entry: wsCommitMain, MainChanged
        timeout_10s → STABLE               # entry: wsCommitMain anyway — current main may be gone
@invariants
  # P3 AST 계약스키마 — phase_3 1st cut per eux-format v1.2 §2.6 (EstreUX 884552b). prose+vocabulary 형식 (Q1=c).
  state:
    - wsAgents 는 동일 agentId 재등록 시 prior conn replace + member-of unique-agentId
    - sourceStampFallback: board-fanout/record event 의 source 는 server-truth (conn.meta.role) IF original.source unset — server-truth invariant (monotonic preservation)
    - telemetry_exclude: codex-watch threadId/runId 인 event 는 _a2aPending 에 never paired + main routing 제외 (member-of exclusion)
    - anonymous_gate: conn.meta.anonymous == true 인 conn 의 relay 는 skip — wsAgents 에 never registered (bounded membership)
    - WS_PRIMARY_ID 는 commitMain transition 으로만 변경 (axis 2 main_handoff machine — monotonic in time)
    - _a2aPending entries 는 RUN_FINISHED 도착 시 closed (state cleanup ordered)
  temporal:
    - _a2aPending 의 모든 pair (req, resp) 는 (resp.t - req.t) within A2A_WINDOW (120s)
    - _selPrompts 의 prompt p 는 p.created + UI6_SERVER_TTL_MS 이전 expires-after (hard-TTL sweep)
    - setMain HandoffRequested 는 10s within HandoffReady 응답 OR timeout fallback (HANDOFF_PENDING → STABLE)
    - relay() 는 at-most-once forward per (msgId, target) — server dedup tier
    - deadlock probe sweep 는 cadence 별 wsEffectiveElapsed 시간 보정 후 wsBuildWaitEdges (after sweep interval) — sweep cadence idempotent (동일 wait edges → 동일 detect 결과)
  transaction:
    - relay() 는 wsToBoards(msg) + wsRecord(msg via -history) 를 always 호출 — ordering atomic (board fanout 과 history 기록이 함께 진행)
    - register(HELLO): 동일 agentId 재등록 시 close+replace prior conn — wsAgents.set persist-before wsPushAgentList broadcast (rollback-safe: 실패 시 prior conn 보존)
    - anti_pattern_ack_storm: relay 는 AckProcessed/ReviewSLAAck never auto-emit — external client 의 idempotent 보장 (server 는 transit 만)
    - setMain commit: WS_PRIMARY_ID = to (persist-before MainChanged.broadcast) — atomic axis 2 transition
    - sourceStampFallback: server stamp commit-then forward (board + record paths)
    - reply-window pairing: msg.targetAgentId 미설정 시 _a2aPending lookup → backfill + dual-write 같은 atomic (board + record + relay)
  causality:
    - register: HELLO.agentId 존재 iff conn.role = 'agent' ∧ wsAgents.has(agentId) post-register
    - handoff commit: WS_PRIMARY_ID == to implies main authority moved (server uninterrupted)
    - deadlock observation: wsBuildWaitEdges (waitingOn/ackFor parse) precedes wsDetectCycles (DFS strict/quasi 분류)
    - escalation: wsDetectCycles cycle 발견 implies wsSurfaceEscalation board emit
@metamorphic
  # P4 property/metamorphic 후보 — phase_3 1st cut per eux-format v1.2 §2.7 (EstreUX 884552b). round-trip/idempotency/determinism.
  round_trip:
    - register(agent) → revoke(agent) → register(agent): wsAgents 동일 endstate (idempotency in roundtrip form)
    - 100x register-then-revoke 동일 agentId: wsAgents 크기 동일 (state preservation)
    - setMain(A) → setMain(B) → setMain(A): WS_PRIMARY_ID == A endstate (handoff round-trip)
  idempotency:
    - anti_pattern_ack_storm: 100x relay 동일 msg 시 AckProcessed 발생 0건 (server idempotent at relay layer)
    - sourceStampFallback: 동일 conn.meta.role 의 stamp 결과 deterministic + idempotent across reconnects
    - telemetry_exclude: codex-watch 분류 결과 deterministic (state.scope == 'codex-watch' OR threadId/runId match)
  determinism:
    - 동일 msg + 동일 fromConn 의 relay() 결과 deterministic (telemetry 분류 + reply-window pairing + sourceStamp 결과 동일)
    - register(HELLO) → wsPushAgentList 의 broadcast 내용 deterministic (wsAgents snapshot ordering)
@operation_discipline
  derive:
    a2a_paired: reply-window backfills targetAgentId for adapters that can't echo the A2A envelope (§13.8)
    source_stamp_truth: server, not client, is authoritative for source role on board-fanout/record paths
    anti_pattern_ack_storm: relay does NOT auto-emit AckProcessed / ReviewSLAAck — those are agent-judgment ack tiers per §13.13 layer split
